name: Collage #2 (Made from Tears)
description: Sweep. Sweep giant scribble I give you my broom, the one I plucked from my chest, the Adam rib bone tied with bristles made from tears – tears made solid and thin like a spider’s web, numbering like the stars bound by compassion. Sweep giant scribble and let the lake wash over you don’t disappear but remember what you were before you were my doubt. Become again what we always are, everything.
